    <note>Chen(1) Jing(12) [27152] I am identifying him as a gentry since his father was a jushi. No address is given for him in wife's funerary inscription, but I am assuming same county although this Chen lineage may be a branch of the distinguished Shaxian Chen(1). His wife, born Yang(2), who married him at age 16 and died in 1119 at age 89, may be related to Yang(2) Shi's lineage, but he gives no indication that this was the case in the funerary inscription. Her father and grandfather are identified as agriculturalists, tianjia, which I take to be farmers. Yang Shi, WJ, 31.11a-12a. Not indexed in CBD.</note>
